<section class="doc-section reglement">
	<h2>WANTERMOART REGULATIONS</h2>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 1:</strong> Organized by the Club des Jeunes Remerschen and Erliefnis Baggerweier a.s.b.l., the Wantermoart takes place at the Baggerweier site – Bréicherwee – L-5441 Remerschen.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 2:</strong> Priority is given to associations and individual artisans for the allocation of market stands. Stand locations are assigned by the organizers.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 3:</strong> As the number of places is limited, each application will be reviewed in the order of receipt and registration. Applicants will be informed of the outcome. Particular attention will be paid to the nature of the products offered, their suitability for a winter market, and the proposed pricing, in order to ensure a balanced and diverse offer for visitors.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 4:</strong> Any exhibitor who sets up on their own initiative before the designated time and/or outside their assigned space will be required to dismantle their stand.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 5:</strong> Opening hours for the public are from 5:00 PM to 10:00 PM on Friday, and from 11:00 AM to 8:00 PM on Saturday and Sunday.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 6:</strong> Exhibitors may access their stands from 10:00 AM to 10:00 PM on Friday and from 10:00 AM to 8:00 PM on Saturday and Sunday. They commit to being present for the entire duration of the event (all three days). Dismantling takes place on Sunday after 8:00 PM and/or on Monday, December 8, 2025, from 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 7:</strong> Organizers may provide certain materials (covered stands, tables, benches, electrical connections, etc.) subject to availability.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 8:</strong> Exhibited items remain the sole responsibility of their owners and must be insured by them. The organizers decline all responsibility for theft, loss, or damage occurring within the event area.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 9:</strong> Exhibitors are civilly liable towards third parties for any accident, damage, or loss caused by their stand or themselves. They also waive any claims against the organizers for any damage or loss, regardless of cause.</p>
	<p class="article-text"><strong>Article 10:</strong> Any violation of these regulations may result in the exclusion of the exhibitor concerned, without any compensation.</p>
	<h3>IMPORTANT NOTE:</h3>
	<p class="article-text">To ensure the proper functioning of the event regarding electricity on our site, and due to the very high consumption that frequently causes outages, we are no longer able to accept electric heaters.</p>
	<p class="article-text">When submitting your application, please inform us precisely of the electrical consumption required for your activity.</p>
	<p class="article-text">Thank you for your understanding and cooperation in ensuring the smooth running of the event.</p>
</section>